<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-14T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/570a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-14T23:00:00-04:00">May 14,
                                    1942—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>112. Please deliver a paraphrase of following secret message signed
                                Marshall<note n="54" xml:id="d501fn54">Gen. George C. Marshall,
                                Chief of Staff, U. S. Army.</note> to Amler<note n="55" xml:id="d501fn55">Code name for Commanding Officer, United States
                                Forces in Liberia.</note> at Harbel.</p>
                        <pb facs="0421" n="409" xml:id="pg_409"/>
                        <p>If the British request further use of facilities which have been granted
                            us in Liberia, they should be informed that the British staff in
                            Washington is the channel through which such a request should be
                            made.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>